Wolves understand that survival depends on a successful hunt.
.
As a result they do not practice panic response management that we as leaders sometimes demonstrate in a crisis.
.
Wolves actually develop a plan working together to insure that they capture and kill their prey. They are extremely patient and understand that success is not guaranteed and that a success rate of 100% is not realistic.
.
Every wolf within the pack has a specific role and they are expected to live up to their responsibility.
.
Approach your business the way Wolves approach their prey, with a plan and a solid team. Never expect 100% success, but always strive for it.

Today, is our first of many anniversaries and I can’t believe how quick time flies, It feels like yesterday I flew out to LA to surprise you for your birthday. Turns out what I thought would be something casual, has now turned into the biggest blessing in my life.

I remember like it was yesterday, waiting for your friends to give me the signal to come surprise you with that one lonely rose, you sitting there looking beautiful as can be, unaware of what was about to happen. Thinking back at it now I laugh at how corny that was, but I think it’s been the simple things like that which have made this relationship all that I could ever ask for, and more than I could imagine.

It hasn’t been an easy journey, we certainly have our differences and well the current miles apart don’t quite help much, but despite all of the things that would weaken most relationships, ours has only gotten stronger, when faced with the decision to move to NY over LA you encouraged me, and made me see things I couldn’t, you weren’t selfish or spiteful. You’ve taught me things which have made me a better man, It’s very rare to meet someone who actually makes you a better person but I am lucky enough to have met you.

Thank you for putting up with all my crazy sh*it and being the understanding, and caring person you are. Thank you for being my better half. I’m sorry I can’t be there today, but I hope the few surprised I have planned for you will make you smile. I Love You @MehreeBee ❤️

In ancient times, people used myths to understand what they saw in the sky. In the murals overhead, 1930s painter Hugo Ballin illustrated those early stories using a parade of Classical ﬁgures.
.
Atlas holds the zodiac signs, followed by the Pleiades, and then Jupiter and his thunderbolts. Venus and the four seasons are next, preceding Saturn, Mercury chasing Argos, and an observer next to a woman holding the Star of Bethlehem.
.
The mural continues on to the Moon and a comet.
Where I am at is merely a point in the path of where I am going.
